00:19:53.033 --> 00:19:57.133
interested in the ultraviolet
over here in today's

00:19:57.133 --> 00:20:01.900
conversation, which starts at
400 nanometers wavelength and

00:20:01.900 --> 00:20:03.767
goes shorter than that.

00:20:07.700 --> 00:20:11.767
And these standard definitions
are helpful.

00:20:11.767 --> 00:20:17.267
UVA are the wavelengths closest
to the visible,

00:20:17.267 --> 00:20:22.467
closest to the blue, defined
as going from 400 to 315

00:20:22.467 --> 00:20:23.600
nanometers.

00:20:23.600 --> 00:20:29.567
UVB, 315 to 280, and then UVC,
