00:20:29.567 --> 00:20:30.833
nanometers.

00:20:30.833 --> 00:20:34.400
Now you may remember from
physics of that the shorter

00:20:34.400 --> 00:20:37.533
wavelength photons are
more energetic,

00:20:37.533 --> 00:20:38.667
they'll do more damage.

00:20:38.667 --> 00:20:45.267
So UVA would cause tanning of
your skin, but probably

00:20:45.267 --> 00:20:48.300
wouldn't give you skin
cancer, UVB might.

00:20:48.300 --> 00:20:51.200
But UVC is very damaging.

00:20:51.200 --> 00:20:54.300
In fact, it's used in
doctor's offices to

00:20:54.300 --> 00:20:57.833
clean surgical tools.

00:20:57.833 --> 00:21:03.367
You put it into this autoclave
which will put UVC on your

00:21:03.367 --> 00:21:06.267
instruments and it'll kill
anything that's there very,

00:21:06.267 --> 00:21:06.967
very quickly.

00:21:06.967 --> 00:21:09.467
It's very damaging radiation.

00:21:12.767 --> 00:21:18.933
And so here's the fate
of UVA, UVB, and UVC.

00:21:18.933 --> 00:21:20.767
Some UVA comes through.

00:21:24.600 --> 00:21:27.967
Half or more of the UVB is
absorbed in the ozone layer,

00:21:27.967 --> 00:21:29.167
plotted on top of this.

00:21:29.167 --> 00:21:35.100
This is altitude and Dobson
