00:21:35.100 --> 00:21:37.133
where the ozone layer is.

00:21:37.133 --> 00:21:41.067
So about 1/2 or 2/3 of the UVB
is absorbed by the ozone.

00:21:41.067 --> 00:21:46.900
And almost all, thankfully, of
the UVC coming from the sun is

00:21:46.900 --> 00:21:49.633
absorbed by the ozone layer.

00:21:49.633 --> 00:21:54.500
So it's a very good protective
shield for us.

00:21:54.500 --> 00:21:58.633
Now what could be changing this

00:21:58.633 --> 00:22:02.867
natural ozone layer situation?

00:22:02.867 --> 00:22:07.133
Well this is the current
theory for it.

00:22:07.133 --> 00:22:12.600
It involves a catalytic reaction
primarily using

00:22:12.600 --> 00:22:18.300
chlorine atoms. Now bromine will
do this as well and there

00:22:18.300 --> 00:22:20.033
is some bromine in the
atmosphere, but I'm going to

00:22:20.033 --> 00:22:23.467
focus strictly on
the chlorine.

00:22:23.467 --> 00:22:25.300
And notice how this
reaction works.

00:22:25.300 --> 00:22:28.133
So you have a chlorine
atom reacting

00:22:28.133 --> 00:22:30.800
with an ozone molecule.

00:22:30.800 --> 00:22:34.267
It goes to ClO, it oxidizes
the chlorine and

00:22:34.267 --> 00:22:36.567
gives you back O2.

00:22:36.567 --> 00:22:41.433
And then quite soon after that,
you'll take this ClO and

00:22:41.433 --> 00:22:45.600
react it with another
ozone molecule.

00:22:45.600 --> 00:22:50.167
That'll give you back the Cl
that you started with and you

00:22:50.167 --> 00:22:55.367
have two O2s, two regular
diatomic oxygens.

00:22:55.367 --> 00:22:57.367
So look, the ozone is gone.

00:22:57.367 --> 00:23:00.067
In fact, two ozones are gone.

00:23:00.067 --> 00:23:04.200
And you've got your Cl back
ready to do it again.

00:23:04.200 --> 00:23:07.500
So this is a catalytic reaction
where the catalyst

00:23:07.500 --> 00:23:10.667
here is the chlorine atom.

00:23:10.667 --> 00:23:14.667
It can be used over and over
again to destroy ozone

00:23:14.667 --> 00:23:16.900
molecules in this way.

00:23:16.900 --> 00:23:20.467
Two ozone molecules are lost
and the catalyst is free,

00:23:20.467 --> 00:23:23.767
ready to go back,
and do it again.

00:23:23.767 --> 00:23:27.900
That's the idea of what's today,
now that we have a

00:23:27.900 --> 00:23:30.467
measurable chlorine
concentration in the

00:23:30.467 --> 00:23:33.367
atmosphere, this is why we
think the ozone layer is

00:23:33.367 --> 00:23:34.733
decreasing.

